# --- Sentry (optional crash reporting for the mobile app) ---
#
# Both the DSN (build-time) and the user's opt-in (in-app toggle,
# in Settings) must be set for any data to be sent. With either
# gate closed, the app does NOT load the Sentry SDK and does not
# make any network calls to sentry.io.
#
# Get a DSN from sentry.io (or your self-hosted Sentry):
#   https://docs.sentry.io/product/sentry-basics/dsn-explainer/
#
# We default this OFF in development. Set the value to a real
# DSN only in production / preview builds.
#
# EXPO_PUBLIC_* vars are inlined at build time and are visible
# in the bundle. The DSN itself is not secret (it's a public
# identifier for a Sentry project), so this is fine.
EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_ENVIRONMENT=development
EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_RELEASE=

# See docs/sentry.md for the full privacy model and the list
# of fields we scrub before any data leaves the device.
